Date: 7 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Alert, 7 Jul 2006
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/060707ESP.htm>

Highly pathogenic avian influenza in wildlife in
Spain: (Disease never reported before in Spain).
Translation of information received on 7 Jul 2006
from Dr Lucio Ignacio Carbajo Goni, Deputy
Director General of Animal Health, Ministry of
Agriculture, Fisheries and Food, Madrid:
Report date: 7 Jul 2006.
Reason for immediate notification: first
occurrence of a listed disease or infection in a country.
Identification of agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza virus subtype H5N1.
Date of start of the event: 30 Jun 2006.
[There is no hint here of the report that the
bird died 6 weeks ago.-- see part [5] below. - Mod.JW]
An outbreak of highly pathogenic avian influenza
in wildlife has been reported in Salburua
wetlands, Alava province (Pais Vasco) in a great
crested grebe (_Podiceps cristatus_) that has been found dead.
The diagnosis has been established by the Central
Veterinary Laboratory at Algete using RT-PCR and sequence analysis.
[Algete is not on OIE's list of Reference
laboratories for HPAI -- see:
<http://www.oie.int/eng/oie/organisation/en_listeLR.htm> - Mod.JW]
The control measures undertaken include -zoning:
a 3-km-radius protection zone around the outbreak
and a 10-km-radius surveillance zone around the
outbreak have been established. There are no
commercial poultry holdings within this
10-km-radius area; within this area, movement of
poultry, other captive birds and their products
is prohibited. Any birds gathering [sic] and any
wild birds game [sic] are also under ban;
[The original Spanish, from <http://www.oie.int/Messages/060707ESP.htm> is:
"... las reuniones o concentraciones de aves y de
la caza de aves silvestres en todas sus
modalidades,", which is better translated as:
".. meetings and concentrations of birds [as in
agricultural or bird fancier shows], and the
hunting of wild birds in all forms, are also under ban." - Mod.JW]
- screening;
- control of wildlife reservoirs;
- surveillance in the natural spaces to detect as
soon as possible any mortality in wild birds.
(1) RT-PCR: reverse transcriptase ï¿½ polymerase chain reaction
